INSERT INTO chunks (id, skill_id, section_title, content, chunk_index, embedding) VALUES (
  '8106ec10-9f41-5c2a-bb74-66af0cf92f19',
  'cd64d82a-46d1-5e20-9656-7b50e0174b22',
  'Common Patterns',
  '### Pattern 1: Temporary Maintenance Mode

Increase timeouts before maintenance, restore after:

```bash
#!/bin/bash
# maintenance-mode.sh

HOST="localhost:26257"

# Enter maintenance mode (increase timeouts)
echo "Entering maintenance mode..."
cockroach sql --host=$HOST --execute \\
  "SET CLUSTER SETTING server.time_until_store_dead = ''15m''"

echo "Performing maintenance operations..."
# Perform rolling restart or other maintenance

echo "Exiting maintenance mode..."
cockroach sql --host=$HOST --execute \\
  "SET CLUSTER SETTING server.time_until_store_dead = ''5m''"

echo "Maintenance complete, settings restored to defaults"
```

### Pattern 2: Progressive Timeout Reduction

Gradually reduce timeouts to find optimal balance:

```sql
-- Week 1: Baseline (default)
SET CLUSTER SETTING server.time_until_store_dead = ''5m'';

-- Week 2: Slightly more aggressive
SET CLUSTER SETTING server.time_until_store_dead = ''4m'';

-- Week 3: Continue reducing if no false positives
SET CLUSTER SETTING server.time_until_store_dead = ''3m'';

-- Week 4: Evaluate metrics, settle on optimal value
-- Monitor:
-- - False positive rebalancing events
-- - Actual failure recovery time
-- - Resource utilization during recovery
```

### Pattern 3: Environment-Specific Configurations

Different environments have different requirements:

```sql
-- Development: Fast feedback
-- server.time_until_store_dead = ''1m15s''

-- Staging: Production-like
-- server.time_until_store_dead = ''5m''

-- Production: Conservative
-- server.time_until_store_dead = ''5m'' to ''10m''

-- DR/Standby: Very conservative (avoid unnecessary rebalancing)
-- server.time_until_store_dead = ''10m'' to ''15m''
```

### Pattern 4: Monitoring-Driven Tuning

Use metrics to inform setting changes:

```sql
-- Check historical rebalancing events
SELECT
  timestamp,
  "eventType",
  info
FROM system.eventlog
WHERE "eventType" = ''range_add_voter''
  AND timestamp > now() - INTERVAL ''7 days''
ORDER BY timestamp DESC
LIMIT 100;

-- If many events during known stable periods:
-- → server.time_until_store_dead is too aggressive
-- → Increase timeout to reduce false positives

-- If recovery from real failures is slow:
-- → server.time_until_store_dead is too conservative
-- → Decrease timeout to speed up recovery
```',
