INSERT INTO chunks (id, skill_id, section_title, content, chunk_index, embedding) VALUES (
  '5a7108ee-ad18-5387-af5f-10b23e44148e',
  'e9cac7bf-e348-5101-9f82-c6970c0fe034',
  'When to Use PITR',
  '### Recovery Scenarios

**Scenario 1: Accidental DELETE**
```
10:00 AM - Production database healthy
10:15 AM - Developer accidentally runs: DELETE FROM orders; (no WHERE clause!)
10:20 AM - Error discovered, need to recover
```

**Solution**: Restore to 10:14 AM (before the DELETE)

**Scenario 2: Bad UPDATE**
```
2:00 PM - Database state correct
2:30 PM - Deployment runs with bug: UPDATE users SET email = ''test@example.com'';
2:45 PM - Bug discovered, all emails corrupted
```

**Solution**: Restore to 2:29 PM (before the bad UPDATE)

**Scenario 3: Unwanted Schema Change**
```
9:00 AM - Database schema stable
9:30 AM - Migration drops critical column: ALTER TABLE DROP COLUMN important_data;
9:35 AM - Realize the column was still needed
```

**Solution**: Restore to 9:29 AM (before DROP COLUMN)',
  2,
