INSERT INTO chunks (id, skill_id, section_title, content, chunk_index, embedding) VALUES (
  'a5139e5c-e2e1-5095-aebe-df9c2e29a0df',
  '6c2517c5-79e9-52c3-943c-4b08f820eac9',
  'Best Practices',
  '### 1. Choose Primary Region Based on User Base

Place primary region closest to majority of users:

```sql
-- Most users in US East
CREATE DATABASE app_db PRIMARY REGION ''us-east'' ...

-- Most users in Europe
CREATE DATABASE app_db PRIMARY REGION ''eu-west'' ...
```

**Why**: Primary region hosts leaseholders by default, reducing read/write latency for primary users.

### 2. Start with Zone Survival, Upgrade as Needed

```sql
-- Start cost-effective
CREATE DATABASE app_db
  PRIMARY REGION ''us-east''
  REGIONS ''us-east'', ''us-west'', ''eu-west''
  SURVIVE ZONE FAILURE;

-- Upgrade when needed
ALTER DATABASE app_db SURVIVE REGION FAILURE;
```

**Why**: Zone survival has lower write latency and storage cost. Upgrade to region survival only when RTO/RPO requirements demand it.

### 3. Use Consistent Naming Conventions

```sql
-- ✅ Good: Matches cloud provider regions
CREATE DATABASE app_db
  PRIMARY REGION ''us-east1''
  REGIONS ''us-east1'', ''us-west1'', ''europe-west1'';

-- ❌ Avoid: Custom names that don''t match infrastructure
CREATE DATABASE app_db
  PRIMARY REGION ''primary''
  REGIONS ''primary'', ''secondary'', ''backup'';
```

### 4. Consider Data Sovereignty Requirements Early

```sql
-- EU-only deployment for GDPR
CREATE DATABASE eu_app
  PRIMARY REGION ''eu-west''
  REGIONS ''eu-west'', ''eu-central'';

-- US-only for domestic compliance
CREATE DATABASE us_app
  PRIMARY REGION ''us-east''
  REGIONS ''us-east'', ''us-west'';
```

### 5. Verify Configuration Immediately

```sql
CREATE DATABASE app_db
  PRIMARY REGION ''us-east''
  REGIONS ''us-east'', ''us-west'';

-- Immediately verify
SHOW REGIONS FROM DATABASE app_db;
SHOW ZONE CONFIGURATION FOR DATABASE app_db;
```

### 6. Plan for Growth

```sql
-- Start with 3 regions
CREATE DATABASE app_db
  PRIMARY REGION ''us-east''
  REGIONS ''us-east'', ''us-west'', ''eu-west'';

-- Easy to add more
ALTER DATABASE app_db ADD REGION ''ap-south'';
ALTER DATABASE app_db ADD REGION ''ap-southeast'';
```',
