INSERT INTO chunks (id, skill_id, section_title, content, chunk_index, embedding) VALUES (
  '1c1eb48a-861f-5c78-819b-93f9a868987e',
  '68e4834a-0470-5b30-b9d4-e0ab840a89a1',
  'When to Use IN PRIMARY REGION vs Specific Region',
  '### Use IN PRIMARY REGION when:

- ✅ Table accessed primarily from application''s main region
- ✅ Primary region may change over time
- ✅ Default behavior acceptable for most tables
- ✅ Simplifying configuration

```sql
-- Flexible - adapts if primary region changes
ALTER TABLE sessions SET LOCALITY REGIONAL BY TABLE IN PRIMARY REGION;
```

### Use IN ''region-name'' when:

- ✅ Strong affinity to specific region (won''t change)
- ✅ Compliance requires data in specific geography
- ✅ Multiple tables in different regions
- ✅ Optimizing for specific regional workload

```sql
-- Fixed - always in eu-west regardless of primary region
ALTER TABLE eu_gdpr_data SET LOCALITY REGIONAL BY TABLE IN ''eu-west'';
```

### Comparison Example

```sql
-- Setup: us-east is primary region
ALTER DATABASE mydb SET PRIMARY REGION ''us-east'';

-- Table A uses PRIMARY REGION (flexible)
CREATE TABLE table_a (id UUID PRIMARY KEY);
ALTER TABLE table_a SET LOCALITY REGIONAL BY TABLE;

-- Table B uses explicit region (fixed)
CREATE TABLE table_b (id UUID PRIMARY KEY);
ALTER TABLE table_b SET LOCALITY REGIONAL BY TABLE IN ''us-east'';

-- Change primary region to us-west
ALTER DATABASE mydb SET PRIMARY REGION ''us-west'';

-- Result: Table A migrates to us-west, Table B stays in us-east
-- Verify with SHOW RANGES FROM TABLE table_a/table_b WITH DETAILS
```',
