INSERT INTO chunks (id, skill_id, section_title, content, chunk_index, embedding) VALUES (
  '7976de7b-5928-5023-8735-7f0eb7b66e37',
  '28b0c72a-66db-5949-b183-d2052b669bbf',
  'Why Non-Voting Replicas Don''t Slow Writes',
  '### Without Non-Voting Replicas (6 Voting Replicas)

```
Write latency = max(RTT to 3 furthest replicas for quorum)

Replicas in: us-east1, us-west1, eu-west1, ap-south1, ap-east1, sa-east1
Quorum = 4 out of 6

RTTs from us-east1:
- us-west1:  70ms
- eu-west1:  80ms
- ap-south1: 200ms  ← Quorum needs this
- ap-east1:  180ms
- sa-east1:  120ms

Write latency ≥ 200ms (waiting for ap-south1)
```

### With Non-Voting Replicas (3 Voting + 3 Non-Voting)

```
Write latency = max(RTT to 1 furthest voting replica for quorum)

Voting replicas: us-east1, us-west1, eu-west1
Non-voting replicas: ap-south1, ap-east1, sa-east1
Quorum = 2 out of 3 voting replicas

RTTs from us-east1 (voting replicas only):
- us-west1:  70ms
- eu-west1:  80ms

Write latency ≥ 80ms (waiting for eu-west1)

Non-voting replicas receive updates asynchronously AFTER commit.
```

**Result**: 200ms → 80ms write latency (60% improvement) while maintaining fast reads globally.',
