INSERT INTO chunks (id, skill_id, section_title, content, chunk_index, embedding) VALUES (
  '0623d98a-8bda-52db-b62b-a0e61add148e',
  '28b0c72a-66db-5949-b183-d2052b669bbf',
  'Limitations of Non-Voting Replicas',
  '### Cannot Become Leaseholder

```sql
-- This will FAIL if attempted on non-voting replica
ALTER TABLE users EXPERIMENTAL_RELOCATE LEASE SELECT 1, 4;
-- ERROR: cannot transfer lease to non-voting replica
```

**Implication**: Writes always coordinated through voting replicas (typically primary region).

### Cannot Participate in Writes

Non-voting replicas:
- ❌ Cannot vote on Raft proposals
- ❌ Cannot acknowledge writes
- ❌ Cannot help achieve quorum
- ✅ Can serve follower reads
- ✅ Can serve `AS OF SYSTEM TIME` queries

### Eventual Consistency Window

Non-voting replicas receive updates asynchronously:

```
Time     Voting Replicas        Non-Voting Replica
0ms      Write committed        (No data yet)
10ms     Replication lag        (No data yet)
50ms     Serving latest         (No data yet)
100ms    Serving latest         ← Receives update
```

**Typical lag**: 10-100ms
**Maximum lag**: Depends on network conditions

### Read Staleness Guarantees

```sql
-- Reading from non-voting replica may be slightly stale
SELECT * FROM countries WHERE code = ''US'';
-- Data may be 10-100ms behind voting replicas

-- Use bounded staleness for guarantees
SELECT * FROM countries AS OF SYSTEM TIME follower_read_timestamp();
-- Guaranteed consistency within bounded interval
```',
