INSERT INTO chunks (id, skill_id, section_title, content, chunk_index, embedding) VALUES (
  '08c96259-cc8b-513c-bb4e-f4c41e30ec98',
  '53189b9e-d3a9-553b-95cb-cdf9a9eb9d62',
  'Configuration Options',
  '### Adjusting Closed Timestamp Target Duration

The default ~4.8 second staleness comes from the `kv.closed_timestamp.target_duration` cluster setting.

```sql
-- Check current setting
SHOW CLUSTER SETTING kv.closed_timestamp.target_duration;
-- Default: 3s (results in ~4.8s actual staleness)

-- Reduce staleness (more frequent closed timestamps)
SET CLUSTER SETTING kv.closed_timestamp.target_duration = ''2s'';
-- Results in ~3.2s staleness, but increases overhead

-- Increase staleness (less overhead)
SET CLUSTER SETTING kv.closed_timestamp.target_duration = ''10s'';
-- Results in ~15s staleness, lower overhead
```

**Trade-offs:**
- Lower values: Fresher follower reads, higher CPU overhead
- Higher values: More stale reads, lower overhead
- Default 3s is good balance for most workloads

### Checking Closed Timestamp Lag

```sql
-- Monitor closed timestamp lag per range
SELECT
  range_id,
  start_key,
  (now() - closed_timestamp)::INTERVAL as closed_ts_lag
FROM crdb_internal.ranges_no_leases
WHERE database_name = ''defaultdb''
ORDER BY closed_ts_lag DESC
LIMIT 10;
```',
