INSERT INTO chunks (id, skill_id, section_title, content, chunk_index, embedding) VALUES (
  'd7789a80-29fa-52e4-ae93-d4a802032508',
  'b3f1b347-c49c-5ab3-9435-6bc964710599',
  'Leaseholder Placement in Multi-Region Deployments',
  'Leaseholder placement is **critical** for multi-region performance:

### Regional Table Locality (REGIONAL BY TABLE)

**Default behavior**: Leaseholders placed in table''s home region.

```sql
-- Set table to live in us-east
ALTER TABLE users SET LOCALITY REGIONAL BY TABLE IN "us-east";
```

**Result:**

```
Range 42 (users table)
  Replicas: Node 1 (us-east), Node 2 (us-west), Node 3 (eu-west)
  Leaseholder: Node 1 (us-east) ← Always in home region

Performance:
  Reads from us-east: ~5ms (local)
  Reads from us-west: ~75ms (cross-region)
  Reads from eu-west: ~150ms (cross-region)
```

**Use case**: Table accessed primarily from one region.

### Regional By Row Locality (REGIONAL BY ROW)

**Per-row leaseholder placement**: Each row''s leaseholder in its home region.

```sql
-- Enable regional by row
ALTER TABLE orders SET LOCALITY REGIONAL BY ROW;

-- Rows automatically include crdb_region column
INSERT INTO orders (id, customer_id, crdb_region)
VALUES (1, 100, ''us-east''),
       (2, 200, ''us-west''),
       (3, 300, ''eu-west'');
```

**Result:**

```
Range 42 (orders, crdb_region=''us-east'')
  Leaseholder: Node 1 (us-east)

Range 43 (orders, crdb_region=''us-west'')
  Leaseholder: Node 2 (us-west)

Range 44 (orders, crdb_region=''eu-west'')
  Leaseholder: Node 3 (eu-west)

Performance:
  Read order 1 from us-east: ~5ms (local leaseholder)
  Read order 2 from us-west: ~5ms (local leaseholder)
  Read order 3 from eu-west: ~5ms (local leaseholder)
```

**Auto-rehoming feature:**

```sql
-- Enable automatic region updates on writes
ALTER TABLE orders SET LOCALITY REGIONAL BY ROW AS crdb_region;

-- When updating from us-west, row''s region automatically updates
UPDATE orders SET status = ''shipped'' WHERE id = 1;
-- crdb_region automatically changes to ''us-west''
-- Leaseholder will move to us-west over time
```

**Use case**: Table with rows naturally partitioned by region (customer region, data residency).

### Global Table Locality (GLOBAL)

**Read-optimized across all regions**: Low-latency reads from any replica.

```sql
-- Set table to global
ALTER TABLE products SET LOCALITY GLOBAL;
```

**Result:**

```
Range 42 (products table)
  Replicas: ALL regions (us-east, us-west, eu-west, ...)
  Leaseholders: Distributed for load balancing

Special behavior:
  - Reads can be served from ANY replica (not just leaseholder!)
  - Uses special "global reads" mechanism
  - Writes are slower (must update all regions)

Performance:
  Reads from any region: ~5ms (local replica)
  Writes: ~150ms (must reach all regions)
```

**Use case**: Read-heavy, infrequently updated data (product catalog, configuration).

### Custom Lease Preferences

**Manual control** over leaseholder placement:

```sql
-- Prefer us-west for leaseholders, fallback to us-east
ALTER TABLE users CONFIGURE ZONE USING
  lease_preferences = ''[[+region=us-west], [+region=us-east]]'';
```

**Result:**

```
Range 42 (users table)
  Replicas: Node 1 (us-east), Node 2 (us-west), Node 3 (eu-west)
  Leaseholder: Node 2 (us-west) ← Honors preference

If us-west unavailable:
  Leaseholder: Node 1 (us-east) ← Uses fallback
```

**Use case**: Override default behavior for specific access patterns.',
